@startuml iterator_paged_repository
title Iterator — Lazy traversal of projects and tasks

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle bold
skinparam backgroundColor white

interface "Iterator<T>" as IteratorT {
  + hasNext() : boolean
  + next() : T
}
interface "Iterable<T>" as IterableT {
  + iterator() : Iterator<T>
}

class "PagedRepositoryIterator<T>" as PagedRepoIter {
  - pageFetcher : Function<Pageable, Page<T>>
  - pageSize : int
  - currentPage : Page<T>
  - inner : Iterator<T>
  - nextPageIndex : int
  + hasNext() : boolean
  + next() : T
  - advance()
}

class ProjectScanner {
  - projectRepository : ProjectRepository
  + iterator() : Iterator<Project>
}

class ProjectTaskTreeIterator {
  - projects : Iterator<Project>
  - taskRepository : TaskRepository
  - currentTasks : Iterator<Task>
  + hasNext() : boolean
  + next() : Task
}

class GlobalReportService <<client>>
class AnalyticsService <<client>>
class ReportService <<client>>

IteratorT <|.. PagedRepoIter
IteratorT <|.. ProjectTaskTreeIterator
IterableT <|.. ProjectScanner

ProjectScanner ..> PagedRepoIter : constructs each iterator()
ProjectTaskTreeIterator --> ProjectScanner : composes
ProjectTaskTreeIterator ..> PagedRepoIter

GlobalReportService --> ProjectScanner
GlobalReportService --> ProjectTaskTreeIterator
ReportService --> ProjectScanner
ReportService --> ProjectTaskTreeIterator
AnalyticsService --> PagedRepoIter

note right of PagedRepoIter
  Constant-memory traversal:
  one DB page at a time, no
  findAll() on the whole table.
end note

@enduml
